At this point, I feel like anything you do is toxic

&quot;Can you gank?&quot; 

&quot;REPORTED FOR BEING TOXIC&quot; 

&quot;Can I get some help mid?&quot; 

&quot;TOXIC REPORTED&quot;

I feel like this community has no idea what half the words they use mean. That, and the mods seem to use it as well, without actuall grasping what it fully means. I&#039;ve seen mods look at things like &quot;Maybe if you weren&#039;t trash going 2-17 initial feeding, maybe we would have won&quot; and saying that&#039;s toxic. It&#039;s really not toxic, at all.

Even things like constructive criticism is toxic, and mods even accept it as toxic. &quot;Look, when you play XXX champion, you need to know that XXX can save your life&quot; &quot;SHUT UP STOP TELLING ME HOW TO PLAY YOU&#039;RE TOXIC AS FUCK SHUT UP&quot; &gt;Mod then nods and says yes you&#039;re toxic

Honestly, this community really needs to stop using this buzzword until they fully understand what it means.

